                    "id": "pollu_benchmark_carbon_radicals",
                    "description": "Classic POLLU air-pollution benchmark (Verwer 1994), carbon, sulfur and radical pools. Same standard POLLU initial state and 0..3600 s window as pollu_benchmark_nox_ozone. Tracks the formaldehyde / aldehyde oxidation chain (CH2O and ALD deplete, CO and CO2 build up), PAN formation, the SO2 -> SO4 oxidation, and the HOx / acetyl-peroxy radical pool. Expected values are an upstream reference run of the GasChem.jl Pollu() ReactionSystem (Rosenbrock23, abstol=reltol=1e-12).\n\nTolerance rationale (test-level rel=1e-5): the ESS scipy-BDF integration reproduces the upstream Rosenbrock23 reference to <=1.1e-7 across every assertion in this test, including the quasi-steady-state radicals HO2, OH and CH3O; rel=1e-5 leaves ample headroom for cross-environment solver-truncation variation.",
